git and GitHub commands:

1.
#checking the if git installed or the version
git --version

2.
#add GitHub email and name
git config --global user.email "put your email"
git config --global user.name "put your name"

3.
#add file or folder to git:
cd /user/...name of folder
#to start git on folder
git init
#checking the status of the repository

# adding file to the stage
git add "file name"
#commit the staging
git commit -m "put a message to the file"

# git add all the files
git add .
# git add all the files from specific type
git add *.txt

4.
# adding a repository from remote site
git remote add origin "internet address"
git push -u origin master

# to checking the file on the repository
git log
